name: Eugenia borinquensis Britton
locality: Mpio. de Rio Grande. Caribbean National Forest, Mt. Britton, Vereda trail, vicinity of lookout tower and adjacent ridgelines.
occurrenceRemarks: Most trees 3-7m tall growing on windswept ridge. Calyx lobes dimorphic, cream colored tinged with red. Petals, anthers, filaments and style all white. Petals with a sweet taste reminiscent of allspice. Bark grayish, rough, occassionally flaking.
